<doc id="579054" wikidata="Q2310134" url="?curid=579054" title="Ōsaka Namba Station">
<text>is a major railway station on the Kintetsu Namba Line and Hanshin Namba Line in the Namba district of Chūō-ku, Osaka, Japan. It is adjacent to Namba Station and JR Namba Station. Trains of the Nara Line depart from and arrive at the station.

==Lines==
Ōsaka Namba Station is served by the following two lines.
* Kintetsu Namba Line
* Hanshin Namba Line

== Station layout ==
The station has an island platform and a side platform with three tracks on the third basement level, parallel to Namba Station on the Osaka Metro Sennichimae Line. There is a returning track in the west of the platforms between the two tracks of the Hanshin Namba Line.

===Platforms===

== Adjacent stations ==




==History==
The station was first named on March 15, 1970, when Kintetsu&#x27;s Namba Line opened. It was renamed to the present name on March 20, 2009, the date of opening of the Hanshin Namba Line.

== Surrounding area ==
*Kintetsu Namba Building
*Midosuji Grand Building
*Dōtonbori
*Osaka City Air Terminal (OCAT)
*Minatomachi River Place (including FM OSAKA)
*Namba Parks, a shopping center and office complex

